 Kylian Mbappe is prepared for his next move away from Paris Saint-Germain as he draws closer to a switch to Real Madrid. The striker is hunting for a house in Madrid as he planned his summer move to La Liga to join Real Madrid. Mbappe’s contract with the Ligue 1 Champions run out in 2022 and it is widely known that the World Cup winner fancies a move to Real Madrid with Los Blancos president Florentino Perez a huge fan of the striker. The striker has stated he wants to focus with PSG to the end of the campaign, though it’s now being claimed he’s preparing to move to Spain. For their part, PSG will be seeking at least €120m to sell. Post Views: 
